(1. Executive Summary) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(TradeZone grew strongly through 2024, with non-cancelled and non-returned quarterly revenue) Tj
T*
(rising from N86.54 million in Q1 2024 to N262.62 million in Q4 2024. However, that growth is) Tj
T*
(uneven: Lagos drives the largest customer acquisition volume, electronics dominate the) Tj
T*
(highest-revenue products, and mid-rated products generate more revenue than high-rated) Tj
T*
(products, which suggests the platform is scaling but not yet converting quality and seller) Tj
T*
(experience into the strongest commercial advantage.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Key Findings) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Growth is heavily led by Lagos, but conversion quality varies by state. Query 1 shows Lagos) Tj
T*
(produced the highest number of 2024 sign-ups with 146 new customers and a 41.78% 30-day) Tj
T*
(conversion rate. FCT followed with 92 sign-ups and a 34.78% conversion rate, while Kano had) Tj
T*
(58 sign-ups but only 25.86% converted within 30 days. This means acquisition volume alone is) Tj
T*
(not enough; TradeZone should treat each state as a separate growth market and focus on) Tj
T*
(improving activation where sign-ups are not quickly becoming buyers.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Revenue accelerated sharply in 2024, with Q4 showing the strongest year-on-year quarterly) Tj
T*
(growth. Query 4 shows Q4 2024 revenue reached N262.62 million across 754 orders, compared) Tj
T*
(with N50.08 million in Q4 2023. This was the strongest revenue growth from 2023 to 2024) Tj
T*
(among all quarters. The result suggests that TradeZone entered 2025 with real commercial) Tj
T*
(momentum, but leadership should check whether Q4 growth came from repeatable demand or from) Tj
T*
(seasonal buying patterns and promotions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Product revenue is concentrated in electronics, while review performance does not perfectly) Tj
T*
(match sales performance. Query 2 shows all top 10 products by 2024 revenue are electronics,) Tj
T*
(led by HP Pavilion 15 Laptop Intel i5 - v2 at N21.23 million. Query 7 shows mid-rated) Tj
T*
(products generated N358.24 million in revenue, more than high-rated products at N258.40) Tj
T*
(million. This is a warning sign for Seller Operations: customers are buying high-value) Tj
T*
(products even when ratings are not the strongest, so poor product or seller experience could) Tj
T*
(become a retention risk if demand continues growing.) Tj
