(4. Data Quality Notes) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The first major issue was inconsistent formatting in city and product category fields. City) Tj
T*
(values included variants such as Lagos, lagos, LAGOS, Lago s and Port-Harcourt, while) Tj
T*
(product categories included misspellings such as Electronis and Fashon. I standardized these) Tj
T*
(values before analysis so state-level acquisition, payment preference and product) Tj
T*
(performance results would not be split across duplicate labels. If this decision was wrong,) Tj
T*
(the biggest impact would be misallocated state or category totals.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The second major issue was missing price information. Four products had missing unit prices,) Tj
T*
(which caused 97 order items to have missing unit prices or line totals and left 92 orders) Tj
T*
(with missing total amounts after recalculation. I did not invent prices; those rows remain) Tj
T*
(flagged in the data_quality_issues view and were excluded from revenue calculations where) Tj
T*
(the total could not be trusted. If the missing prices later turn out to be material, total) Tj
T*
(revenue and product rankings would be understated.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5. What the Data Cannot Tell Us) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The current dataset cannot explain why certain customers fail to purchase within 30 days) Tj
T*
(after signing up. It shows the conversion outcome by state, but it does not include) Tj
T*
(marketing channel, campaign exposure, app or website session behavior, discount usage,) Tj
T*
(product views, cart activity, delivery fee estimates or customer support contacts. To answer) Tj
T*
(that business question, I would request acquisition-channel data, campaign spend and) Tj
T*
(impressions, behavioral funnel events, discount and promotion records, and customer support) Tj
T*
(interaction data linked to customer_id and signup_date.) Tj
